cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.HC 

This paper is focused on natural language understanding datasets and the impact of annotator bias on model performance. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper discusses machine learning models and their ability to recognize productive annotators, which suggests a potential fit for cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also touches on the importance of monitoring annotator bias in dataset creation, which could be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
